node.text:
I get a lot of questions about the Disability Access Service aka DAS so here ya go! PLEASE DO NOT ABUSE THIS SYSTEM! It is put in place to assist individuals like Evan and Eli. I also want to dispel the myth that those utilizing this service don’t stand in lines because that is NOT true. We DO stand in the lines, but receive a return time so much of our wait time has been somewhere else (sitting down, using the restrooms, going to First Aid, etc). I hope you enjoy the video!
.
.
.

node.text:
Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.
.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.

node.text: I risked my life for some hand sanny today and met a T-Rex in the process. I am so so thankful for the generosity of these complete strangers ❤️ I’m a front line worker and have NO hand sanitizer. They reached out to me and we met at the Target on Harbor Blvd. near Disneyland! Keep spreading kindness, y’all!

This is your daily reminder not to believe everything you see on social media 😉 It took me 40 years to feel comfortable in my own skin. Funny thing is, I’ve never been fatter, had more wrinkles, or that much gray poking out of my scalp 👵🏼 And ya know what? I could care less! I stopped wearing makeup a couple years ago (I think I only put it on on my birthday) & have really grown to love my bare face. I’m no longer self conscious when taking photos & seeing myself on camera no longer makes me cringe. People ask me all the time how I deal with hate comments and it’s really in much the same way I dealt with my own insecurities…age. Getting older, I just care less about the things that don’t matter and more about the things that do. I honestly wish I could’ve lived in this mindset in my 20’s and 30’s because I’m far more happy now than I was then 😊 Be happy, friends 🌸 Life’s too short to worry about the bullshit 🤌🏽 Oh and in case you’re wondering, I like the pic on the left waaaaay more than the one on the right (which is completely edited…not a drop of actual makeup on my face) 😋

In true McLeod Fam fashion I had to turn this mess into a TikTok 😂 Let’s be honest, it wouldn’t be us if it wasn’t translated in TikTok 🤣🤣 Disney still has NOT released my money so it is very much still being held against my bank balance 💵 I am aware that this has happened to sooooo many other families and I am so so sorry y’all are having to deal with this, too 😢 I hope this video makes you laugh (or cry less in my case) 😉 Disneygate 2021 will forever live in infamy!

On a side note, I could really go for some mini muffins right now 🤤

Something that should’ve been such an exciting experience has turned into a nightmare 😭 I know there are other families out there like ours who were all charged multiple times and I am so so sorry if you’re feeling the same way I am right now. Sending each of you so much love 💗 And to be clear, I am not upset bc I didn’t get something I wanted. I am upset because my account thousands of dollars pending against it AND my kids will likely miss out on an experience I have been working MONTHS to afford them 😢 Disappointed in @disney today 😔
